# Student LMS Coding Guidelines

## Core Standards
- Use TypeScript strict mode patterns; avoid `any` unless absolutely necessary.
- Reuse existing components, utilities.
- Prefer `shadcn/ui` and Radix UI primitives wherever possible before building custom UI from scratch.
- Prefer icons from a maintained icon library (for example, `@phosphor-icons/react`) over image URLs or custom icon assets wherever possible.
- Keep components focused and readable; extract reusable logic when duplication appears.
- Keep file size minimal; max file length is 200 lines. Split into smaller components/hooks/utils when approaching this limit.
- Handle edge cases explicitly (empty states, invalid inputs, null/undefined values).

## Testing Requirements
- Add or update tests for every non-trivial behavior change.
- Prefer behavior-driven tests with Testing Library over implementation details.
- Cover positive path, fallback/edge case, and critical UI state transitions.
- Keep tests deterministic; avoid timing-sensitive assertions where possible.

## Styling and UX
- Follow existing Tailwind and component style conventions in the same feature area.
- Avoid hardcoded magic values when a project token or shared constant exists.
- Preserve accessibility basics (semantic elements, interactive affordances, readable text).

## PR Quality Bar
- Ensure `npm run test` and `npm run lint` pass for touched code.
- Keep changes scoped to the request; do not refactor unrelated areas.
- Add concise code comments only where logic is non-obvious.
